				Introducing The			
Breakthrough, real-time clinical decision and patient monitoring devices.







				Products			


We have identified a number of indications that would benefit from an automated ultrasound measurement and from these indications we have selected our first two monitoring devices to develop which are closely integrated into our high level strategy.
 

BBS Revolution™ device

The BBS Revolution™ device, our first product, is an automated bladder volume measurement device. The BBS Revolution™ Scanner is a small, handheld device which is used to make a rapid, automated measurement of a patient’s bladder volume. The enhanced features of the BBS Revolution™ device will allow an easier and more rapid bladder measurement when compared with competing devices – while eliminating costly calibration and maintenance.
Learn More          Download PDF Brochure
 
StatCVP™ Monitor
The StatCVP™ Monitor is a truly novel device that provides a noninvasive assessment of Central Venous Pressure and Total Blood Volume. The StatCVP™ Monitor utilizes the sophisticated dBMEDx ultrasound core to automatically monitor the 3D geometry of the inferior vena cava and aorta. The StatCVP™ Monitor is simple to use, incredibly powerful and will not only revolutionize the triage of critical care patients in the ER but is designed to be used beyond the hospital by any medical professional in any setting including EMTs, first responders and military field medics. The market for the StatCVP™ Monitor is significant, encompassing every hospital and EMS globally.
Learn More



















dBMEDx Inc Closes Second Round of Funding





















